a dinosaur is a reptile while a human is a mammal. The body of a dinosaur and human are very different. While some dinosaurs were carnivorous, most were herbivorous. Therefore it is possible that a carnivorous dinosaur might have had the ability to chew. Generally speaking, animals are considered carnivorous if they have the ability to chew. If an animal lacks the ability to chew, it may be considered herbivorous. Therefore a herbivorous dinosaur would not be classed as carnivorous.
